This paper focuses on natural language generation, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The methods proposed in the paper involve using web resources to extract linguistic information, which could also fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The evaluation of the methods involves comparing the generated texts to manually authored linguistic resources, which could be considered a machine learning (cs.LG) task. Finally, the paper deals with ontologies, which are often used in databases (cs.DB).
